<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-09-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-09-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="364" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d364">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Shah of Persia</gloss> to
                                President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-09-20"><hi rend="italic">September 20,
                                    1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>On the occasion of the accession of your excellency to the Presidency I
                            sincerely congratulate you, and express the best wishes that I make for
                            your happiness and the prosperity of the United States.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Mozaffer ed
                            Dine</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>